first_reading.text:
[[Sg 6,12]]Resplendent and unfading is Wisdom, and she is readily perceived by those who love her, and found by those who seek her.
[[Sg 6,13]]She hastens to make herself known in anticipation of men's desire;
[[Sg 6,14]]he who watches for her at dawn shall not be disappointed, for he shall find her sitting by his gate.
[[Sg 6,15]]For taking thought of her is the perfection of prudence, and he who for her sake keeps vigil shall quickly be free from care;
[[Sg 6,16]]Because she makes her own rounds, seeking those worthy of her, and graciously appears to them in the ways, and meets them with all solicitude.
